id: pm-d4ns
title: "Sentry PM-CLI-2B: external extension subprocess cannot resolve pm executable"
description: Investigate and correctly attribute the single handled spawnSync pm ENOENT event emitted by an external readPmItems extension command. Determine the owning package and replace PATH-dependent recursive CLI invocation with the public pm SDK or an explicit executable contract; prevent downstream extension failures from being attributed as high pm-cli core errors without hiding actionable failures.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: "area:observability",external-integration,sdk-adoption,sentry
created_at: "2026-07-14T13:16:38.180Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-15T13:31:53.135Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-15T13:31:24.347Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 120
acceptance_criteria: Identify the emitting extension/package and release; remove or harden the PATH-dependent spawnSync pm call in the owning repository; use the public SDK where appropriate; PM-CLI-2B no longer blocks the pm-cli Sentry gate; document fresh event and telemetry evidence.
parent: pm-5oj5
risk: medium
confidence: 70
resolution: Released PATH-independent pm executable resolution in pm-changelog@2026.7.15-1 and resolved the stale pre-fix Sentry group after clean publish/install proof.
expected_result: pm-changelog item reads invoke the installed pm-cli binary without relying on a globally discoverable pm executable.
actual_result: pm-changelog@2026.7.15-1 resolves the package binary through process.execPath; PM-CLI-2B has no recurrence and the live Sentry gate reports zero highs.
